<paragraph id="B9643694F418FFCCFF52F876FEA2EB66" blockId="0.[151,1436,1978,2040]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="426" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">
The grass-feeding thrips 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F418FFCDFE71F876FDE9EDF3" authorityName="Ananthakrishnan" authorityYear="1967" box="[436,574,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Amalothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8BAFEA86F418FFCDFE71F876FDE9EDF3" box="[436,574,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Amalothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises two Asian species, 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F418FFCDFC5BF876FBD4EDF3" authorityName="Ananthakrishnan" authorityYear="1967" box="[926,1027,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Amalothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaccidus">
<emphasis id="8BAFEA86F418FFCDFC5BF876FBD4EDF3" box="[926,1027,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">flaccidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F418FFCDFBF8F876FB61EDF3" box="[1085,1206,1978,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Amalothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noorazlani">
<emphasis id="8BAFEA86F418FFCDFBF8F876FB61EDF3" box="[1085,1206,1978,2004]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">noorazlani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is the first record of the genus from 
<collectingCountry id="C1CC7604F418FFCDFE63F812FE3BEDDF" box="[422,492,2014,2040]" name="China" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">China</collectingCountry>
, and includes one new species and one new record. Members of 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F418FFCDFB11F812FA89EDDF" authorityName="Ananthakrishnan" authorityYear="1967" box="[1236,1374,2014,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Amalothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8BAFEA86F418FFCDFB11F812FA89EDDF" box="[1236,1374,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="425">Amalothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been distinguished from other genera by having a simple sense cone on antennal segments III and IV, and the head strongly projecting in front of the eyes in both sexes (
<bibRefCitation id="DD4A4B65F419FFCCFD29FF77FC84EAF2" author="Ng, Y. F." box="[748,851,186,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" pagination="246 - 250" refId="ref3899" refString="Ng, Y. F. (2015) A new species of Amalothrips Ananthakhrishnan from Malaysia, with first description of male. Zootaxa, 4032 (2), 246 - 250. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4032.2.13" type="journal article" year="2015">Ng 2015</bibRefCitation>
). However, a third species is described here with the sense cone forked on antennal segments IIIâ€“IV. This difference in sense cones among species is surprising, but such variation is also known in other genera that are associated with 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F419FFCCFC99FECFFC6CEB3A" baseAuthorityName="Mound &amp; Tree" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[860,955,259,285]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F419FFCCFBF3FECFFB6FEB3A" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1836" box="[1078,1208,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Chirothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8BAFEA86F419FFCCFBF3FECFFB6FEB3A" box="[1078,1208,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Chirothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7EDB4D17F419FFCCFB28FECFFABFEB3A" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1836" box="[1261,1384,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Limothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8BAFEA86F419FFCCFB28FECFFABFEB3A" box="[1261,1384,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Limothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="DD4A4B65F419FFCCFF52FEEBFEBDEB66" author="Mound, L. A. &amp; Collins, D. W. &amp; Hastings, A." box="[151,362,295,321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refId="ref3773" refString="Mound, L. A., Collins, D. W. &amp; Hastings, A. (2018) Thysanoptera Britannica et Hibernica - Thrips of the British Isles. Lucidcentral. org, Identic Pty Ltd, Queensland. Available from: https: // keys. lucidcentral. org / keys / v 3 / british _ thrips / (accessed 5 July 2021)" type="url" year="2018">Mound et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
